long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: 1. ssh -X remote-box 2. virt-manager 3. run a virtual machine 4. open virtual machine window 5. crash
if i run strace -f virt-manager i get: [pid 23172] write(2, "\n(virt-manager:23172): GSpice-CRITICAL **: egl init failed: cannot create EGL context\n", 86) = 86
presumably virt-manager should be able to cope without GL on remote X?
Version-Release number of selected component: virt-manager-1.4.0-3.fc24
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.7.2 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/bin/python2 /usr/share/virt-manager/virt-manager crash_function: _XGetRequest executable: /usr/bin/python2.7 global_pid: 20160 kernel: 4.7.4-200.fc24.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 73BD E983 81B4 6521 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1043
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 0 (7 frames) #9 _XGetRequest at XlibInt.c:1702 #10 XCreateWindow at Window.c:118 #11 _gdk_x11_display_create_window_impl at gdkwindow-x11.c:1109 #12 gdk_window_ensure_native at gdkwindow.c:1787 #13 gdk_x11_window_get_xid at gdkwindow-x11.c:5544 #14 spice_egl_realize_display at spice-widget-egl.c:326 #16 drawing_area_realize at spice-widget.c:581
Looks like this comes from spice-gtk. Can you still reproduce with latest package versions on the remote host?

(In reply to Cole Robinson from comment #13) > Looks like this comes from spice-gtk. Can you still reproduce with latest > package versions on the remote host?
One could also test with our copr repo at https://copr.fedorainfracloud.org/coprs/g/spice/nightly/
I think this was fixed by https://cgit.freedesktop.org/spice/spice-gtk/commit/?id=a395ac59447dedfb922f997c7c9cff93edd53600

Thanks victor, that makes sense, as the patch is in f24 with the 0.32-3 version, which is around when correlates with the slow down of faf reports. So I'm closing this, but if anyone is still reproducing with latest f24/f25 packages on the remote host, please reopen.

on Fedora 25 i can't reproduce this bug, thanks for fixing.
